- content_for :title do
  Privacy Policy
- set_meta_tags(title: "Privacy Policy",
                description: "Corsego's privacy policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information on our online learning platform.",
                type: "website",
                url: privacy_url)

.container
  .card.shadow
    .card-header
      %h1.h3
        Privacy Policy
    .card-body
      %p
        This Privacy Policy describes how Corsego ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use our website
        = succeed "." do
          %a{:href => "https://corsego.com"} corsego.com

      %h2.h5 1. Information We Collect
      %p We collect information you provide directly when you:
      %ul
        %li Create an account (name, email address, profile image)
        %li Enroll in courses (payment information processed securely via Stripe)
        %li Create and publish courses as an instructor
        %li Leave comments, ratings, and reviews
        %li Contact us for support
      %p We also automatically collect certain technical information when you visit our site, including your IP address, browser type, pages visited, and time spent on pages.

      %h2.h5 2. How We Use Your Information
      %p We use the information we collect to:
      %ul
        %li Provide and maintain our learning platform
        %li Process enrollments and payments
        %li Track your course progress and issue completion certificates
        %li Send you important account notifications
        %li Improve our platform and develop new features
        %li Prevent fraud and ensure platform security

      %h2.h5 3. Payment Processing
      %p All payment transactions are processed through Stripe. We do not store your credit card details on our servers. Stripe’s privacy policy governs the handling of your payment information.

      %h2.h5 4. Third-Party Services
      %p We use the following third-party services that may collect information:
      %ul
        %li
          %strong Stripe
          — payment processing
        %li
          %strong Amazon Web Services (AWS)
          — file storage and email delivery
        %li
          %strong Google Analytics
          — website usage analytics
        %li
          %strong OAuth providers (Google, GitHub, Facebook)
          — authentication, only when you choose to sign in with these services

      %h2.h5 5. Data Retention
      %p We retain your personal information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you with our services. You may request deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us.

      %h2.h5 6. Data Security
      %p We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal information, including encrypted connections (HTTPS), secure password hashing, and restricted access to personal data.

      %h2.h5 7. Your Rights
      %p You have the right to:
      %ul
        %li Access the personal information we hold about you
        %li Request correction of inaccurate information
        %li Request deletion of your account and personal data
        %li Withdraw consent for optional data processing
        %li Export your data in a portable format

      %h2.h5 8. Cookies
      %p We use cookies to maintain your session, remember your preferences, and understand how you use our platform. You can configure your browser to reject cookies, though this may affect some platform functionality.

      %h2.h5 9. Children’s Privacy
      %p Our platform is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.

      %h2.h5 10. Changes to This Policy
      %p We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes by posting a notice on our website or sending you an email.

      %h2.h5 11. Contact Us
      %p If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at #{mail_to "support@corsego.com"}.

      %p.text-muted.mt-4 Last updated: January 1, 2025
%br